#: R/likertplot.b.R
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<h3>Data & Sorting</h3>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li>Likert variables must be of ordinal measure-type. (Continuous "
"measure-type works as well.)</li>\n"
"<li>If you plan to compute mean/median/sd or to use comparison tests, they "
"must be of integer data-type.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Tidy up levels:</strong> when checked, try to fix the labels "
"order in table and graph (when some variables miss some levels).</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Convert variables to integer:</strong> when checked, the level "
"labels are ignored and only integer values are used.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Sort Variables by Median:</strong> orders the list of Likert "
"variables by median.</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<h3>Comparison Tests</h3>\n"
"<p>When using a group variable, several tests are available:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Mann-Whitney U:</strong> Two group comparison</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Kruskal-Wallis:</strong> n group comparison</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Post Hoc Tests:</strong> Dunn, Conover and "
"Dwass-Steel-Critchlow-Fligner (DSCF) paiwise comparisons tests.</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>The p-values can be adjusted <strong>groupwise</strong> (for each "
"question) for post hoc tests or <strong>overall</strong> (groupwise and "
"questionwise) for MannWithney U, Kruskal-Wallis and post hoc tests. DSCF "
"p-values are already adjusted (groupwise); no other adjustment is "
"possible.</p>\n"
"<p>A sample file is included at Open > Data Library > vijPlots > Likert</p>"
msgstr ""
"<h3>Podatki & Urejanje</h3>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li>Likertove spremenljivke morajo biti tipa ordinalne mere. (Tudi "
"kontinuierne mere delujejo.)</li>\n"
"<li>Če načrtujete izračun povprečja/mediane/standardnega odmika ali uporabo "
"primerjalnih testov, morajo biti tipa celoštevilskega podatka.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Počistitev ravni:</strong> kadar je označeno, poskuša popraviti "
"vrstni red etiket v tabeli in grafu (ko nekaterim spremenljivkam manjkajo "
"nekatere ravni).</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Pretvorba spremenljivk v celoštevilske:</strong> kadar je "
"označeno, se etikete ravni ignorirajo in uporabljajo se samo celoštevilske "
"vrednosti.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Urejanje spremenljivk po mediani:</strong> ureja seznam "
"Likertovih spremenljivk po mediani.</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<h3>Primerjalni testi</h3>\n"
"<p>Ko uporabljate skupinsko spremenljivko, so na voljo naslednji testi:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Mann-Whitney U:</strong> primerjava dveh skupin</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Kruskal-Wallis:</strong> primerjava n skupin</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Testi post hoc:</strong> Dunn, Conover in "
"Dwass-Steel-Critchlow-Fligner (DSCF) parne primerjalne teste.</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>P-vrednosti je mogoče prilagoditi <strong>po skupinah</strong> (za vsako "
"vprašanje) za teste post hoc ali <strong>skupno</strong> (po skupinah in "
"vprašanjih) za teste Mann-Whitney U, Kruskal-Wallis in teste post hoc. DSCF "
"p-vrednosti so že prilagojene (po skupinah); ni mogoče izvesti nobene druge "
"prilagoditve.</p>\n"
"<p>Primer datoteke je vključen v Open > Data Library > vijPlots > Likert</p>"

#: R/corresp.b.R
msgid ""
"<p>This module computes <strong>Correspondence Analysis (CA)</strong> for "
"two categorical variables. Computations are based on <a href = "
"\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=FactoMineR\" "
"target=\"_blank\">FactoMineR<a/> package by F.&nbsp;Husson, J.&nbsp;Josse, "
"S.&nbsp;Le, J.&nbsp;Mazet.</p>\n"
"<p>The data can be</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li>an <strong>Observation table</strong> (raw data), possibly weighted "
"using <em>jamovi</em> built-in weight system or using the \"Counts\" "
"variable</li>\n"
"<li>or a <strong>Contingency table</strong></li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p><strong>Supplementary row or column</strong> numbers may be entered as "
"integer lists : 1,3,6</p>\n"
"<p>Four normalizations (scaling of row and column scores before plotting) "
"are avalaible :</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Principal:</strong> Row an columns scores are scaled by "
"eigenvalues.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Symmetric:</strong> Row an columns scores are scaled by the "
"square root of eigenvalues. </li>\n"
"<li><strong>Row Principal:</strong> Only row scores are scaled by "
"eigenvalues.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Column Principal:</strong> Only column scores are scaled by "
"eigenvalues.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Standard:</strong> The raw coordinates without "
"normalization.</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>A sample file is included at Open > Data Library > vijPlots > Smoking</p>"
msgstr ""

#: R/multcorresp.b.R
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<p>This module computes <strong>Multiple Correspondence Analysis "
"(MCA)</strong> for several categorical variables. Computations are based on "
"<a href = \"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=FactoMineR\" "
"target=\"_blank\">FactoMineR<a/> package by F.&nbsp;Husson, J.&nbsp;Josse, "
"S.&nbsp;Le, J.&nbsp;Mazet.</p>\n"
"<p>Both classic methods are available:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Indicator matrix:</strong> CA of the indicator matrix</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Burt matrix:</strong> CA of the Burt matrix. The eigenvalues are "
"the squares of those of the indicator matrix method. </li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>Both methods give the same <em>standard</em> coordinates (but different "
"<em>principal</em> coordinates).</p>\n"
"<p>When selected, <strong>Benzécri and Greenacre corrections</strong> are "
"applied to eigenvalues only (<strong>Summary</strong> table). Coordinates "
"(and inertia) of categories and observations are computed from the original "
"eigenvalues of the Burt matrix.</p>\n"
"<p>The <strong>Normalization</strong> options specify how the coordinates "
"are scaled (by eigenvalues):</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Principal:</strong> Both category and observation coordinates "
"are scaled.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Category principal:</strong> Only category coordinates are "
"scaled.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Observation principal:</strong> Only observation coordinates are "
"scaled.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Standard:</strong> Both category and observation coordinates are "
"standard.</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>A sample file is included at Open > Data Library > vijPlots > Cars</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p-Ta modul izračuna <strong>Multiple Correspondence Analysis (MCA)</strong> "
"za več kategorialnih spremenljivk. Izračuni so temelji na <a href = "
"\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=FactoMineR\" "
"target=\"_blank\">FactoMineR<a/> paketu avtorjev F.&nbsp;Husson, "
"J.&nbsp;Josse, S.&nbsp;Le, J.&nbsp;Mazet.</p>\n"
"<p>Na voljo sta obe klasični metodi:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Indikatorska matrika:</strong> CA indikatorske matrike</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Burtova matrika:</strong> CA Burtove matrike. Lastne vrednosti "
"so kvadrati tistih iz indikatorske matrike metode. </li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>Obe metodi dajeta iste <em>standardne</em> koordinate (vendar različne "
"<em>glavne</em> koordinate).</p>\n"
"<p>Ko je izbrana, se uporabljajo <strong>Benzécri in Greenacre "
"popravke</strong> le za lastne vrednosti (<strong>Povzetek</strong> tabela). "
"Koordinate (in inertia) kategorij in opazkov so izračunane iz prvotnih "
"lastnih vrednosti Burtove matrike.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Normalizacija</strong> možnosti določajo, kako so koordinate "
"merjene (z lastnimi vrednostmi):</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Glavna:</strong> Koordinate kategorij in opazkov so "
"merjene.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Kategorija glavna:</strong> Le koordinate kategorij so "
"merjene.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Opazka glavna:</strong> Le koordinate opazkov so merjene.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Standardna:</strong> Koordinate kategorij in opazkov so "
"standardne.</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>Primer datoteke je vključen pri Odpri > Knjižnica podatkov > vijPlots > "
"Avti</p>"

#: R/principal.b.R
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<p>This module computes <strong>Principal Component Analysis (PCA)</strong> "
"for several continuous variables. Computations are based on "
"<tt>stats::prcomp</tt> function.</p>\n"
"<p>Although rotated components are not principal components, they are widely "
"used. Only orthogonal rotations are available (from GPArotation "
"package).</p>\n"
"<p>Loadings (variable coordinates) and scores (observation coordinates) are "
"principal (scaled by the squareroot of eigenvalues).</p>\n"
"<p>Biplot follows \"Biplots in Practice\" (Michael Greenacre, 2010):</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Form biplot:</strong> Scores are principal (scaled by "
"eigenvalues) while loadings are standard.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Covariance biplot:</strong> Loadings are principal while scores "
"are standard. </li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p><strong>Advanced options</strong>:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Standardize loadings:</strong> loadings are normalized with sums "
"of squared equal to 1 (instead of eigenvalues)</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Standardize scores:</strong> scores are normalized with "
"variances equal to 1 (instead of eigenvalues)</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Rotate eigenvectors:</strong> the rotation (varimax, etc) is "
"applied to eigenvectors (standard loadings) instead of principal loadings "
"(STATA way).</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>A sample file is included at Open > Data Library > vijPlots > Iris</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p-Ta modul izračuna <strong>Glavne komponentne analize (PCA)</strong> za "
"več kontinuiranih spremenljivk. Izračuni temeljijo na funkciji "
"<tt>stats::prcomp</tt>.</p>\n"
"<p>Čeprav rotirane komponente niso glavne komponente, so v široki uporabi. "
"Na voljo so samo ortogonalne rotacije (iz paketa GPArotation).</p>\n"
"<p>NagIBi (koordinate spremenljivk) in rezultati (koordinate opazovanj) so "
"glavni (standardizirani z razdaljo kvadrata iz lastnih vrednosti).</p>\n"
"<p>Dvogradbeni graf sledi „Dvogradbenim grafom v praksi“ (Michael Greenacre, "
"2010):</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Oblika dvogradbenega grafa:</strong> Rezultati so glavni "
"(standardizirani z lastnimi vrednostmi), medtem ko so nagibi "
"standardni.</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Kovarijantni dvogradbeni graf:</strong> Nagibi so glavni, medtem "
"ko so rezultati standardni.</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p><strong>Napredne možnosti:</strong></p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Standardiziraj nagibe:</strong> nagibi so normalizirani z vsoto "
"kvadratov, enakih 1 (namesto lastnih vrednosti)</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Standardiziraj rezultate:</strong> rezultati so normalizirani z "
"variancami, enakimi 1 (namesto lastnih vrednosti)</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Rotiraj lastne vektorje:</strong> rotacija (varimax itd.) se "
"uporabi za lastne vektorje (standardne nagibe) namesto glavnih nagibov "
"(način STATI).</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>Primer datoteke je vključen v Odprto > Knjižnica podatkov > vijPlots > "
"Iris</p>"

#: R/mrfrequencies.b.R
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<p>This module computes frequencies for multiple response questions, also "
"known as \"Check All That Apply\" (CATA) questions.</p>\n"
"<p>Questions may be coded as:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li>several <strong>dummy (or indicator) variables</strong> using 0/1, 1/2, "
"Y/N for each possible answer;</li>\n"
"<li>a single <strong>multi-valued variable</strong> containing the checked "
"answers, separated by a symbol (usually \",\" or \";\").</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>A sample file is included at Open > Data Library > vijPlots > Credit "
"Cards</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p-Ta modul izračunava frekvence za večodgovorne vprašanju, znane tudi kot "
"\"Check All That Apply\" (CATA) vprašanju.</p>\n"
"<p>Vprašanja se kodirajo kot:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li>več <strong>navideznih (ali indikatornih) spremenljivk</strong> z "
"uporabo 0/1, 1/2, Y/N za vsak možen odgovor;</li>\n"
"<li>ena <strong>večvredna spremenljivka</strong>, ki vsebuje označene "
"odgovore, ločene z znakom (običajno \",\" ali \";\").</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>Primer datoteke je vključen v Open > Data Library > vijPlots > Credit "
"Cards</p>"

#: R/mrcrosstabs.b.R
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<p>This module computes two-way frequencies for multiple response questions, "
"also known as \"Check All That Apply\" (CATA) questions.</p>\n"
"<p>Questions may be coded as:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li>several <strong>dummy (or indicator) variables</strong> using 0/1, 1/2, "
"Y/N for each possible answer;</li>\n"
"<li>a single <strong>multi-valued variable</strong> containing the checked "
"answers, separated by a symbol (usually \",\" or \";\").</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>A sample file is included at Open > Data Library > vijPlots > Credit "
"Cards</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p-Ta modul izračuna dvosmerne frekvence za večodgovorne vprašalne (tudi "
"imenovane \"Check All That Apply\" (CATA) vprašalne).</p>\n"
"<p>Vprašalne lahko kodirajo:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li>več <strong>dummy (ali indikatorskih) spremenljivk</strong> z uporabo "
"0/1, 1/2, Y/N za vsak možen odgovor;</li>\n"
"<li>eno <strong>večvredno spremenljivko</strong>, ki vsebuje označene "
"odgovore, ločene z znakom (običajno \",\" ali \";\").</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>Primer datoteke je vključen pri Odpri > Knjižnica podatkov > vijPlots > "
"Kreditne kartice</p>"

#: R/qqplot.b.R
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<p>This module uses <a href = \"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=qqplotr\" "
"target=\"_blank\">qqplotr R package<a/> by Alexandre Almeida, Adam Loy and "
"Heike Hofmann. In-depth information can be found in the package "
"documentation on CRAN site.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Reference line:</strong> Draws either the <em>identity line</em> "
"(y = x) or the commonly-used <em>Q-Q line</em> that intercepts two data "
"quantiles (Q<sub>0.25</sub> and Q<sub>0.75</sub>). P-P plot only supports "
"identity line.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Confidence band:</strong> Draws a confidence band around the "
"reference line. qqplotr package provides several methods to compute the "
"confidence band:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong><em>Pointwise</em></strong> constructs pointwise confidence "
"bands based on Normal confidence intervals;</li>\n"
"<li><strong><em>Bootstrap</em></strong> creates pointwise confidence bands "
"based on a parametric bootstrap;</li>\n"
"<li><strong><em>Kolmogorov-Smirnov</em></strong> band is based on the "
"Kolmogorov-Smirnov test;</li>\n"
"<li><strong><em>Tail-Sensitive</em></strong> constructs a tail-sensitive "
"confidence bands but is only implemented for Normal Q-Q plots;</li>\n"
"<li><strong><em>Equal Local Levels (ELL)</em></strong> constructs "
"simultaneous bands using the equal local levels.</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>P-P plots only support \"ELL\" and \"Bootstrap\" methods.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Detrended plot:</strong> The objects are <em>detrended</em> "
"according to the reference line. This procedure may help reducing visual "
"bias caused by the orthogonal distances from the points to the reference "
"line.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Parameter values:</strong> The distribution parameters can be "
"estimated from data using:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Maximum Likelihood Method</strong> (using MASS package) : it "
"should work with all distributions but \"t\" and \"uniform\";</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Method of Moments</strong> for moment based parameters : it "
"should work with \"normal\", \"log-normal\", \"Beta\", \"Exponential\", "
"\"Gamma\", \"Logistic\" and \"Uniform\" distributions;</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>or entered by user:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Parameter 1:</strong> mean (Normal), meanlog (Log-normal), "
"shape1 (Beta), location (Cauchy, Logistic), df (Chi-squared, Student), df1 "
"(F), rate (Exponential), shape (Gamma, Weibull) and min (Uniform);</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Parameter 2:</strong> sd (normal), sdlog (Log-normal), shape2 "
"(Beta), scale (Cauchy, Logistic), df2 (F), rate (Gamma, Weibull) and max "
"(Uniform).</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p-Ta modul uporablja <a href = "
"\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=qqplotr\" target=\"_blank\">qqplotr R "
"paket<a/> avtorjev Alexandre Almeida, Adam Loy in Heike Hofmann. Podrobne "
"informacije so na voljo v dokumentaciji paketa na spletni strani CRAN.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Referenčna črta:</strong> Riše ali <em>identitetno črto</em> (y = "
"x) ali pogosto uporabljano <em>Q-Q črto</em>, ki preseka dve kvantili "
"podatkov (Q<sub>0,25</sub> in Q<sub>0,75</sub>). P-P graf le podpira "
"identitetno črto.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Pozitivna območja:</strong> Riše pozitivno območje okoli "
"referenčne črte. Paket qqplotr ponuja več metod za izračun pozitivnega "
"območja:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong><em>Točkasti</em></strong> gradi točkaste pozitivne območje na "
"podlagi intervalov zaupanja Normal;</li>\n"
"<li><strong><em>Bootstrap</em></strong> ustvari točkaste pozitivne območje "
"na podlagi parametričnega bootstrapa;</li>\n"
"<li><strong><em>Kolmogorov-Smirnov</em></strong> območje temelji na "
"Kolmogorov-Smirnovovem testu;</li>\n"
"<li><strong><em>Občutljivost na rep</em></strong> gradi občutljiva na rep "
"pozitivna območja, vendar je implementirana le za Normal Q-Q grafe;</li>\n"
"<li><strong><em>Enake lokalne ravni (ELL)</em></strong> gradi sočasna "
"območja z uporabo enakih lokalnih ravni.</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>P-P grafi podpirajo le metodi \"ELL\" in \"Bootstrap\".</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Detrendirani graf:</strong> Objekti so <em>detrendirani</em> "
"glede na referenčno črto. Ta postopek lahko pomaga zmanjšati vidne "
"pristranosti, ki so povzročene z ortogonalnimi razdaljami od točk do "
"referenčne črte.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Vrednosti parametrov:</strong> Parametri porazdelitve lahko "
"ocenimo iz podatkov z:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Metoda maksimalne verjetnosti</strong> (z paketom MASS): bi "
"moral delovati z vsemi porazdelitvami, razen \"t\" in \"enakomerno\";</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Metoda momentov</strong> za parametre, ki temeljijo na momentih: "
"bi moral delovati z „normalno“, „log-normalno“, „Beta“, „eksponentno“, "
"„Gamma“, „logistično“ in „enakomerno“ porazdelitvijo;</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"<p>ali ga je mogoče vnesti ročno:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"<li><strong>Parameter 1:</strong> povprečje (Normal), meanlog (Log-normal), "
"shape1 (Beta), lega (Cauchy, Logistic), df (Chi-kvadrat, Študent), df1 (F), "
"hitrost (Eksponentna), oblika (Gamma, Weibull) in min (Enakomerno);</li>\n"
"<li><strong>Parameter 2:</strong> standardna deviacija (normalna), sdlog "
"(Log-normal), shape2 (Beta), merilo (Cauchy, Logistic), df2 (F), hitrost "
"(Gamma, Weibull) in maks (Enakomerno).</li>\n"
"</ul>\n"
"</p>"

